ref_comments: Volunteer Driver Program - Orange County Department on Aging  This service is for people ages 55 and over who are too frail for other forms of transportation or for whom there is no other option. Registration is required; trips are free. The rider must be able to get in and out of a car with minimal help. Drivers do not transport wheelchairs but can borrow a wheelchair at the medical office . Call the Transportation Specialist (919-717-1853) to register and request rides.  BUS: Orange County Public Transportation  The Hillsborough Circulator stops near UNC Hospital in Hillsborough, UNC Family Practice, and Duke Primary Care.    The Orange-Chapel Hill Mid-Day Connector (420) stops at UNC Hospital in Hillsborough and Chapel Hill and the ACC in Chapel Hill.
